Sentencas: A finite element model (FEM) was developed which is able to calculate and predict the electrical performance of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with a three dimensional interface between cathode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: An enlargement of the electrochemical active surface leads to a significant increase of the electrical performance of a SOFC.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Various three dimensional electrolyte/electrode interfaces have been realized by first screen printing of individual 10YSZ particles onto a flat and dense 8YSZ substrate.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Surface enlargements between 10 and 50% have been realised and investigated.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Second, a screen printed cathode (LSM) layer was applied as a current collector and gas distribution layer.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: In order to develop a FEM-model for this type of cathode/electrolyte interface, several electrical properties of cathode (LSM) and electrolyte (8YSZ) were examined.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Further on, measurements of symmetrical cells (LSM/8YSZ/LSM) to evaluate the electrode resistance R-0 were carried out for different symmetrical cells.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Taking into account the enlargement of the interface surface, electrical conductivity and electrode resistance R-0, the entire DC polarisation-resistance R-pol could be calculated by FEM.
Titulo: Modelling and DC-polarisation of a three dimensional electrode/electrolyte interface
